Company Description
Lenna.AI is an AI-powered Conversational platform that automates millions of customer interactions. Our platform helps businesses grow by enhancing their customer experience through automation.

Role Description
This is a full-time on-site role in Tangerang for a DevOps Engineer. The DevOps Engineer will be responsible for:
Deploying, automating, maintaining various cloud-based
 production systems;
Maintain and improve our Cl development pipeline;
Work closely with product operations team to ensure that we
 are adopting security best practices;
Creating, versioning and testing of scripts for backup, deployment,
 patching and etc;
Ensuring the availability, performance scalability and security of
 production systems;
Building & releasing configuration management of production
 systems;
System troubleshooting and problem-solving across platform
 and application domains;
Building monitoring capabilities for existing systems;
Ensuring system security policies are properly remediated;
Set up and maintain cloud security solutions.

Qualifications
1 years of DevOps or related experience;
BS/MS Degree in any relevant major (e.g. IT, Computer Science,
 etc) OR a proven track record in DevOps;
Evidence of understanding networking concepts. VPC, network
 segmentation, ingress-egress configuration, VPN connection,
 router configurations;
Experience in Docker and Kubernetes;
Strong command of English, both verbally and in writing;
Familiar with AWS services.
